Has Verant given up on the PvP servers?<br><br>It seems that it has, as bugs and exploits known for MONTHS have neither <br>been fixed or dealt with in any manner.<br><br>The following short-list of bugs and or exploits off the top of my head that <br>have been ignored by Verant.<br><br>Mez bug.  If an enchanter assumes the race of the person they are attacking <br>and mez's that person it causes that person to remain mez'd even when they <br>are hit until the mez's duration wears off.<br><br>Illusion bug.  Many spells will not work on someone in the same form as the <br>person that is attacking or they have attacked.<br><br>Illusion bug #2. You cannot loot the person even if you kill them if they <br>are in the illusion form of the same race as the person that killed them.<br><br>The Illusion bugs also occur when the person is using the item Mask of the <br>deceiver.<br><br>Rogue pet syndrome.  If you send pet to attack another player, and use egg <br>shaped pumice against them at the same time, the pet goes rogue and becomes <br>an NPC. The pet then hits for full damage, and causes exp loss if it kills <br>the player or the mage himself. People without honor can cause the pet to go <br>rogue on purpose in an attempt to cause exp loss to the other player.<br><br>Permanent invisible Pet.  A not so well known exploit, I would offer <br>information to the designers if they would like it but would rather not post <br>it to keep it from being abused even more. Its affect is to cause a pet to <br>become invis. Permanently. When it attacks mobs or players. While I have <br>never used this against someone, this is a VERY exploitable bug in PvP.<br><br>Now, I'm sure there are more bugs/exploits than this.  And some of these <br>*MIGHT* have been fixed, but I have heard nothing to suggest they have. <br>Please Verant, fix these long standing problems on the PvP servers. While <br>we may not have huge server populations, we are customers and should receive <br>service on these problems.<br><br>Thank you for your time.<br><br>Poldara Flamingfist<br>52nd Elementalist<br>Vallon Zek

