10. You've seriously considered filling out credit card applications with the <br>name of your EQ character, thinking it'd be 'cool'. <br><br>9. You buy foraged veggies, rabbit, meatpies, milk, water, bread, cupcakes, <br>iron rations, and other assorted food because you want to make sure your <br>character has a balanced diet. Yet in real life, you live on McDonalds and <br>Dominos. <br><br>8. After getting some phat loot from the City of Mist, you would think <br>nothing of running all the way to Kelethin just to sell that item. Yet when <br>your spouse, girlfriend or mom asks you to pick something up from the store, <br>you complain about how it's 'out of the way'. <br><br>7. You've actually drawn pictures of your character while at work, school, <br>detention, or whatever. <br><br>6. After fighting with your wife or girlfriend over how much you play EQ, you <br>finally get her calmed down. You wait until she sleeps, then sneak out of <br>room to play more EQ. <br><br>5. You have EQVault, Everlore, EQlizer and AllaKhazam all bookmarked. <br><br>4. The idea of being home alone, ordering pizza, having the Matrix or some <br>WWF stuff running on TV as you EQ-the-night away gives you 'warm fuzzies'. <br><br>3. You've stopped using marijuana, heroin, crack or cocaine because you were <br>afraid it would impair your abilities to play EQ effectively. <br><br>2. You had a great dream about getting that phat god or dragon loot, but when <br>you woke up and realized that it was only a dream, you got annoyed because <br>you didn't really get that loot afterall. <br><br>1. A typical day for you is-You play EQ all night. Go to work, while at work, <br>surf the net for EQ news, stop by the message boards to read more on EQ <br>happenings on your server, go home, have dinner by your PC while playing EQ, <br>tell your group you have to go AFK for 10 minutes, shower, and play EQ the <br>rest of the night. 

