With the addition of the Iksar race, there is much debate as to why Iksar are KOS to all other races. This is an attempt to address this issue by looking at historical events in our world to understand why the Iksar are KOS to all of Norrath. <br><br>OK. Look at the discovery of Kunark from this angle. When the Europeans discovered the Americas, they encountered Indians, Aztecs, Incas, Mayans, and more. The natives had established cities, especially the Incas, Aztecs and Mayans. You draw a comparison to Cabilis here. When the Europeans explored the new continent, they found a culture foreign and barbaric to them. They witnessed virgin sacrifices, the killing of a woman every morning to make the sun rise, the drinking of blood, and more. The Europeans did not say, "Hey, go board our ships and check out Europe. It's a neat place." The Europeans slaughtered them. It was very rare for an American Indian to travel to Europe and walk around freely. It was until the late 1500s/early 1600s before American Indians were taken to England under the guise of freedom (Read the factual tale of Pocahontas). What I am getting at here is that, Iksar would naturally be KOS in all foreign lands, at least for a long period. If, the Aztecs got on a ship and traveled to London, they would probably be imprisoned. Or, if a whole bunch of Powhatan Indians ran to Jamestown to try to get on a ship to England, they would have been captured or killed. You can draw a parallel to a bunch of Iksar attempting to get on the boat at Firiona Vie. They are killed. <br><br>We do not have to look only at the "discovery of the New World" to understand why Iksars are KOS. Just look at Feudal Japan. The governments prohibited all contact with Europeans and others. Christians were killed when they came to the docks. It was not until President Millard Filmore sent warships to Japan, demanding they open up, that Europeans were safe to travel there. On the other hand, look at Africa. Not only were tribes KOS to each other, but Whites were KOS to everyone. European outposts for the slave trade were established on the coast, but rarely did Europeans travel into the mainland. <br><br>In addition to this, the fact that one race worships the same religion as the other does not matter. WWI and WWII had nations whose foundations are based in Christianity on both sides. In Mid-evil Europe, Christianity did not keep the British and the French from fighting. <br><br>To carry all this further, just because you are "Good" or "Evil", does not mean you will like other people of the same alignment. Whether Native Americans, Aztecs or Incas were "evil" or not is in the eye of the beholder. Native Americans sure as hell thought the Europeans were evil when they began slaughtering them (Yes, some Indian nations were at times at peace with Europeans, but not for ever). Iksar consider the other races to be "evil" because they seek to invade their homeland. The Ogres, Elves, Humans, ET al. are trying to take what remains of the once great Iksar empire. The Humans, Elves, Ogres, etc. see the Iksar trying to rebuild the Iksar Empire. They fear domination too. I am not saying that Indians, Aztecs, Africans or Japanese are like the Iksars, nor am I saying that they are "evil". I am just using these historical events to illustrate the current situation on Norrath. <br><br>-Taronga Kingfisher 

