<P>
Chapter 2<br><br>&#8220;&#8230; and the violence escalates with each day.   We have sent word to Rivervale for assistance,  but the trek from Freeport to Rivervale grows more dangerous each day.  We have yet to receive any response.&#8221;  Crayth Nalison reported via magic communications portal.<br><br>Lady Jeyna Sleighhill sat among the Council of Elders in Felwithe as they listened to Paladin Crayth Nalison&#8217;s report.    It has been seven years since the death of Jeyna Sleighhill&#8217;s husband, Seron.   In that time,  the Sleighhill family has been honoured by being declared nobility by the Elven Council of Elders out of respect for Seron Sleighhill and his life&#8217;s work against the evils of Norrath.    Seron&#8217;s body was returned to Faydark and buried in the Elven temple of nobles.  During the funeral service,  Jeyna Sleighhill gave new meaning to the name &#8220;Ocean of Tears.&#8221;  However, true to Seron&#8217;s word,  young Darien Sleighhill was growing up strong.  Already at a young age,  Seron Sleighhill possessed an uncanny ability in the arts of Melee combat and some skill in the Clerical arts.  The council predicted Darien Sleighhill would become a fine Paladin,  however,  Jeyna sensed something different in her son that the others could not see. <br><br>&#8220;The news is indeed grim.&#8221; Jonark Crablinyth,  high council leader remarked.   &#8220;Has word been sent to the High Humans in Erudin?&#8221;<br><br>&#8220;It has,  my liege.&#8221;  Crayth Nalison reported grimly.  &#8220;However,  the Erudites have informed me that they are having serious problems with the Erudite Heretics.   The Humans in Freeport face a similar problem, as human Necromancers and Shadow Knights continue to assist the Teir&#8217;dal in East Commons.   There has been no luck searching out the Human Necromancer or Shadow Knight guilds here in Freeport.&#8221;<br><br>The council began to talk amongst themselves.   The news was indeed grim in Antonica.  The Teir&#8217;dal gained in strength with each passing day.  Like an unstoppable avalanche in the mountains of Everfrost Peak,  anything in the path of the Teir&#8217;dal was overrun and destroyed.  Finally,  council member Jonas Saradin, high mage responded.<br><br>&#8220;We will send additional Elven warriors and mages to Antonica.   They will arrive in five days.   In the meantime,  maintain your surveillance and report to the Council should anything significant arise.  May Tunare watch over you.&#8221;  Jonas Saradin replied.<br><br>Crayth Nalison gave a slight bow,  as the magical communications portal shimmered then closed.   The Council hall was deathly silent.  The news had not been good over in Antonica.   It seemed as if nothing did any good against the Dark Elves.   It would only be a matter of time before they breached the security of the island of Faydwer.   Finally,  Jeyna Sleighhill broke the silence.<br><br>&#8220;The Emerald Warriors should be informed&#8230;  as should the Magic Guild here in Felwithe&#8230;&#8221;  Jeyna Sleighhill said with a heavy heart.  <br><br>&#8220;I will inform my fellow mages.&#8221;  Jonas Saradin said grimly.  The council hall fell silent again.  The Elven High Council had been stunned silent.  Suddenly,  the council doors burst open, as young Darien Sleighhill ran into the hall with weapon drawn.<br><br>&#8220;Come back here and I will let you taste my blade!  Hee hee hee!&#8221;   Darien Sleighhill exclaimed gleefully.<br><br>&#8220;Young Lord Sleighhill&#8230; what is the meaning of this?&#8221;  Jonark Crablinyth asked.<br><br>&#8220;Darien!  You cannot just barge into the Council hall while a meeting is in session.  How many times have I told you?&#8221;  Jeyna Sleighhill said sternly to her over-energetic son.<br><br>&#8220;But Mother&#8230; I could have sworn that I saw an orc pawn run in here.&#8221; Darien protested.<br><br>&#8220;I assure you,  young Darien.  There are no orcs in this chamber.&#8221;  Jonas Saradin said in the lowest of tones.   This was not the first time that young Darien let his imagination get the better of him.<br><br>&#8220;Darien,  run along and play outside.  Do not wander too far from the city guards.   I expect you home in time for supper though.  Do not be late.&#8221;   Jeyna told her son.<br><br>&#8220;Yes mother.&#8221;  Darien replied reluctantly as he exited the Council hall.   <br><br>&#8220;I am so terribly sorry&#8230;.&#8221;  Jeyna began to apologize.   Jonark Crablinyth dismissed her with his hand.<br><br>&#8220;Don&#8217;t be.  Never before have I seen such fighting spirit in one so young.  Your son is very special.&#8221; Jonark remarked.<br><br>&#8220;He must have gotten it from his father&#8230;.&#8221; Jeyna replied as her thoughts began to drift to Seron.<br><br>	Darien stormed out of Felwithe and kicked the dirt at his feet.  He could have sworn that he saw a Crushbone Orc Pawn running through the halls of Felwithe.   The image had been so clear.   As clear as the crystal blue sky that blanketed Faydwer this sunny day.   This was not the first time that Darien saw things that were not really there,  yet Darien insisted that what he saw was real.  Two months ago,  Darien ran into the council hall claiming that Ogres and Trolls had reached the shores of Butcherblock.  When a scouting party was sent,  no trace of such a force was found.   Half a year ago,  Darien claimed to have saw Lord Nafagen attacking Kelethin and burning the city to the ground.   Of course,  the great wyrm was nowhere near the wood elf city when a scout was sent to investigate.  <br><br>&#8220;Stupid council&#8230;.  Always having meetings&#8230; what good do they do anyway.&#8221;  Darien grumbled as he stomped through the mud.   Suddenly,  Darien heard a cry for help.  He looked around for the city guards,  but they were nowhere in sight.    Darien followed the sound of the cries and came upon a Crushbone Orc Pawn attacking a young elven female,  who was about Darien&#8217;s age,  perhaps slightly younger.  At first,  Darien shook his head and rubbed his eyes,  thinking he was over-imagining again.   However,  the image looked so real.  He had to do something.  Darien drew his sword and his shield.  He had never fought a real orc before.  His mother would not allow it.<br><br>&#8220;Stick to bats and wasps&#8230;.&#8221;  Jeyna had warned him sternly.   But it was time now to test his skills against a stronger opponent.    The orc raised his fist high in the air and prepared to bring it down on the elven female&#8217;s fragile head.   <br><br>&#8220;Me crush you now puny elf.  Muahahahahaha&#8221;  the orc laughed.<br><br>Darien stopped the blow with his shield and kicked the orc squarely in the gut.  The orc doubled over in pain<br><br>&#8220;Argh!  Elves like you have ruined your land!  You&#8217;ll not ruin mine!&#8221;  the orc taunted as he prepared to strike at Darien.<br><br>Darien assumed a defensive posture and parried the orc&#8217;s attacks with relative ease.  As the orc began to tire from swinging with all his might against his elven foe,  Darien went on the offensive.  He brought his sword down hard across the orc&#8217;s torso and sliced it open.  Blood spilled on the soil as the orc screamed in pain and grabbed at his open wound.   Suddenly,  a blast of frost struck the orc and brought him to his knees.   Sensing an opportunity to finish off his enemy,  Darien swung his sword and sliced off the orc&#8217;s head clean off his body.  The orc slumped to the ground lifeless.   Behind Darien,  the young elven female was panting heavily, with one hand raised in front of her.  It was obvious to Darien that the frost bolt had come from her.<br><br>&#8220;Thank you&#8221; Darien said.<br><br>&#8220;No thank you.  My name&#8217;s Eralyn Goldshadow. Apprentice wizard.&#8221;  Replied the elf.<br><br>&#8220;I&#8217;m Darien.  Darien Sleighhill.  What are you doing so far from the city guards?&#8221;  Darien asked.<br><br>&#8220;I wanted to pick some flowers for my mother.   I became kind of lost&#8230;&#8221;  Eralyn said.   &#8220;Do you know where we are?&#8221;<br><br>Darien looked around.  His surroundings were unfamiliar<br><br>&#8220;No,  I don&#8217;t.  I don&#8217;t know how to get back home.&#8221;  Darien said glumly.  Suddenly,  he heard a rustling in the bush.   <br><br>&#8220;Did you hear that?&#8221;  Darien asked?<br><br>&#8220;No,  what?&#8221;  Eralyn said with concern.  &#8220;What&#8217;s wrong?&#8221;<br>&#8220;Ssshh&#8230;&#8221;  Darien hushed.   Suddenly,  a vision came before Darien&#8217;s eyes.  He was several orcs striking down at Eralyn and himself.   When Darien&#8217;s regular vision return,  Eralyn&#8217;s eyes were wide with fear.  <br><br>&#8220;Look out!&#8221;  Eralyn screamed<br><br>The last thing Darien felt was the end of a mace come crashing down on his head.<br><br>	Darien was slowly regaining consciousness.   He struggled to move,  but he found himself tied down to a table.  Surrounding him were three Crushbone Orc Legionnaires.   Eralyn was tied to a table next to him,  a bloody mess.   Darien noticed however that her midsection was rising and falling slowly.  She was still breathing,  she was still alive.   Darien struggled against his restraints and tried to free himself.<br><br>&#8220;Do not move, elf,  or me crush your head again.&#8221;  The Orc Legionnaire warned.  &#8220;You our prisoner in Crushbone now.   You do what we say.&#8221;<br><br>The door to the room opened, as a Teir&#8217;dal in fine ornamental robes entered the room.<br><br>&#8220;Good day children.  My name is Ambassador D&#8217;vinn.   You are in Emperor Crush&#8217;s castle.  You do know who Emperor Crush is,  don&#8217;t you?&#8221;<br><br>&#8220;I tire of listening to you speak.  My people will come for me, and when they do,  you will all be sorry&#8230;&#8221;  Darien spat at the Dark Elf. <br><br>&#8220;You know what,  my little elven friend?   We are counting on it.&#8221;  Ambassador D&#8217;vinn replied.   D&#8217;vinn then made a gesture with his hand at a mirror on the wall.   An image formed in the mirror.<br><br>&#8220;Yes,  what is it?&#8221;  the Dark Elf in the mirror asked.  Darien turned to look at the mirror.  The elf in the mirror was young,  barely out of his teens.  Darien did not know this elf,  but the elf seemed strangely familiar to him&#8230;<br><br>&#8220;Lord D&#8217;eewlay.   We have captured the son of Sleighhill.   May we proceed with the next phase?&#8221; D&#8217;vinn asked.<br><br>&#8220;Argh.  He is too young.   You were supposed to wait&#8230;.&#8221;  Blair D&#8217;eewlay admonished.<br><br>&#8220;A orc hunting party found him and a companion next to a slain orc.   The Legionnaires were ready to kill him.  I had no choice but to stop them and take him and his friend prisoner if our plan is to succeed.&#8221;  D&#8217;vinn explained.<br><br>Lord D&#8217;eewlay consulted with several unseen Dark Elves.   Finally,  after several minutes of deliberation,  Blair replied.<br><br>&#8220;This turn of events is unfortunate.   We must now accelerate our plans.   Begin the next phase.&#8221;  Blair ordered.<br><br>&#8220;As you wish,  my lord.   What shall we do with the children?&#8221; D&#8217;vinn asked.<br><br>&#8220;When their usefulness has expired,  kill them immediately.&#8221;  Blair replied in a cold tone<br><br>Darien&#8217;s heart dropped into his stomach.   Inside,  he was thankful that Eralyn was not conscious to hear what the Dark Elves had to say.<br><br>End of Chapter 2<br><br>Send all comments and suggestions to <a href="mailto:kma@julian.uwo.ca">kma@julian.uwo.ca</a>

