<SPAN CLASS="pagesub">Ancestors of EverQuest</SPAN><br>
<img src="/images/topback.jpg" valign="bottom" width=475 height=2><br>
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Author:</SPAN> 
<span class="credit2">Hawkril  (<a href="mailto:hawkril@hotmail.com" class="credit2">hawkril@hotmail.com</a>)</SPAN>&nbsp;&nbsp;  
<SPAN CLASS="credit">Organization:</SPAN> <a href="" class="credit2">N/A</a><br>

<SPAN CLASS="regtext">
<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
Today, most of the average gamers would look at this game and think to themselves, "Damn, this game blows away any other online game out there!" But the games that lead up to this great game should be the ones getting the respect and thanks that gamers give to those who created EverQuest. We will start off back in the most modern gaming system that had any kind of multi-player ability to the games we play now. <P>Some of the older game players might remember back when the big new thing was Atari. With its joystick like controller and its cartridge games it revolutionized and started the gaming world. One of the most basic games that we play may have started the multi-player world. That game would be Pong. Yes you read that right Pong. You may think that I am joking but this is one of the first games to let two friends duke it out one on one in a video game. Pong may look the worst graphic enhanced game yet the people that had Atari were going crazy for the games. PitFall may be one of the first games to have any kind of adventure and exploring in it. Atari hit it big everywhere it was. After a while though the system became so popular that other companies wanted to get in on the money they were making at Atari. <P>The next big thing was the first 16-bit systems that took the video gaming world into a whole new league. Nintendo and the Sega broke into the average person's homes and made the outside look dim. Kids would sit and play games such as Sonic, Mario Bros., Zelda, and even the many sports games out there. Soon enough Nintendo and Sega were breaking records for sales in a day and week as soon as the record was made. Nintendo started up its own magazine soon which started other groups to make ones. Some magazines reviewed both systems games while others only reviewed one systems game. One game that is still going strong started its legacy off here. Some of you may not know but Ultima Online is the complete combination of all the Ultima games leading back to the original one which first ht stands right after the Nintendo did. Ultima is probably one of the longest on going sagas ever to be created. With Nintendo and Sega keeping up with the demand for more and better games decided to bring out the big boys. <P>With the two big names still fighting and now splitting the game world they introduced Super Nintendo and another Sega. These both were now 32-bit systems. With these games sagas continued in better graphics, better sound, and an easier control. About the same time as this the computer world was beginning to pop up with some big hits. Some of their big games were games such as Wolfenstein 3D, MineSweep, and even the basic card games. With the three systems now competing for the spotlight they started to pump out games that had no meaning to it or were games that had topics that no one wanted. Sega tried to jump the gun and threw out Sega Saturn that ended up being a huge mistake. With the fluke here Sega went straight into hiding and let Sony jump in and introduce its new system Playstation. With its huge new graphics and brand new 3D games it made people go nuts. Nintendo was shoved start down to number 2 as Sony took the people to new worlds with their system. The computer world was now just getting into the Internet world and beginning to make contact with areas never talked with before. <P>Nintendo didn't take long to pull out of its Super Nintendo crazy and shoot for Number 1 again. They jumped bandwagon and produced the new N64. This is the time when EverQuest's ancestors began their long journey to the top. With new computer games now coming out every month and the Internet now becoming one of the biggest things since the invention of the phone or wheel. Most of the games at this time were either over the top or still in a 2D. This may seem like a laugh now but we all started of playing the games like Command and Conquer, Doom, and Diablo. These games help introduce the Internet world to the people. C&C started it off with the modem games where you connect to your friend's computer and the play. This kind of connection is used by many games till. Diablo and its maker Blizzard started off probably the first Internet community game. People would log into the Battle.net and then go straight into joining games. Followers and other groups who started this were groups like M Player, Heat.net, and The Zone. The zone would probably be the biggest multi-player community because of its number of games it has under its belt. Then from the bulging blocks of these Ultima Online was created. The first fully Internet based game.<P>Ultima Online sent gamers into the world of Britannia and let them go wild and let their minds wander on what their character should be. With this game setting the stage for it all EverQuest took the idea but created the fully 3D, fully Internet, first shooter, and largest map area ever done.  <P>EverQuest was created not from scratch but was a building process from the beginning of gaming itself.  The game may be the best damn Internet game ever but it wouldn't be where it is without the creations of the original gaming system and the Internet. In my opinion this game is the icon of everything that has ever been created to make a video game better. This game takes eliminate from the original game Pong to the games we play now and combined them all into one and came up with the world we now play in of Norrath. If there were going to ever be a better game I would have to put my money onto a second EverQuest.  

