<!-- Begin Content -->
<P>
An update to bring you regarding the <a href="http://www2.eqvault.com/lore/admin/viewnews.cgi?newsid955557279,96791,">article</a> we posted yesterday.  Former Guide Desmo sent me the following letter telling his side of the story and included a log of the events and an email he sent to the GM regarding his account:<UL><P>Here's what happened last Thursday night on Lanys.... <P>First some background information. There had very recently been an influx of new guides into the program, myself being one of them. We had been accepted as Apprentice Guides about two weeks prior, and most of the new Appies had just been promoted to full Guide status on Wednesday. Of the Guides that got banned, me (Desmo) and Valdul were very fresh new recruits. Another effect of all the new Guides (about 5 or 6 new, plus the original group of however many) meant that the petition que was very low every time I logged into Lanys. All of the new Guides were "camping" the que so we could get experience answering petitions and have something to do. <P>At the time of the event, the que was totally empty. There were an abundance of Guides online, I'll guess about eight at all times. Ozzadyen mentioned over the guide channel that he was gonna check out the Arena zone and see if anyone was there. He soon informed us that there were over 30 people in the zone, most high level players of the Solidaire guild. He suggested we should go in hidden and start swinging. Note that this wasn't a preplanned event, and that the normal GM of the server wasn't online at the time. I was the first to join him, he was already fighting when I got there. I jumped in beside him and started beating on people with my Swords of Guidance. My strategy was too not kill anyone, and target people that were "taunting" me or trying to draw my attention. Throughout the first round of melee, I had fun trading jests with the other players and I don't think I killed anyone. <P>After awhile, about 25 minutes, I stopped attacking and said I would go outside the PvP area and answer questions that anyone might have. Sort of an informal Answer Circle. That went on for a little while, everyone was doing a good job RP'ing and the mood was very happy and playful. Somehow me and another Guide were set up for a duel, and players were placing having fun placing bets on who would win (me of course :p ). So Valdul and I headed back into the Arena again and faced off, with many players watching. Of course a fully buffed Guide can not be killed, so the duel was for fun anyway. By now the other Guides had shown up, and a duel between Calais the Gnome Kicker and a certain gnome rogue started up. It actually ended with Calais being slain, since he didn't have his GM buff (shapechange50, which grants a whole bunch of hp's and an incredible regen rate. As a warrior I had around 13,500 hp's, and was recovering them at easily 300-500 per tick, in other words, invincible) and Guide equipment isn't really made for fighting. Everyone got a kick outta seeing a corpse with a green name :). Soon another free for all broke out, and everyone was still having a great time. I think I did slay someone this time. I targeted someone who had low hitpoints and didn't notice it until it was too late. If you are reading this, I'm sorry about that, I didn't mean too :( After awhile I called a stop again and we all met up outside the PvP area again for more talk. <P>Note that during this entire time, the que was still be watched by other Guides who weren't in the Arena, and I was also keeping an eye on it myself during the fights. For those that don't know, the GM interface is a transparent overlay that you can have up and still play normally. At no time did anyone to my knowledge complain about what we were doing, quite the opposite in fact. People really seemed to love it, and us Guides were having a blast as well. I was thanked multiple times by players saying they were having a great time. Then things took a turn for the worse. <P>A GM from another server showed up, although I didn't notice at first. I was still talking to players while this new GM was over talking to Ozz. He was just out of range of /say's so I don't know what was said. I soon figured out something was up when all the players starting showing concern for us. That's when I noticed the other GM. Soon after we were all brought to cshome and told to sit down. I'll paste in the transcript below of what we were told, and only edit out the unnecessary stuff. Quite honestly, I didn't know that what we did was wrong. I had been a full Guide for less than 24 hours, and the idea for the Arena event came from the senior Guide on the server. During the verbal lashing we got, they pointed out where it says in the PnP (Guide rule book) that we can't fight other players. The statement is under a section called No Hunting/ Questing/ Crafting/ Shopping/ Begging/ Etc. The section does not stand out in any way from the rest of the book. The sentence that says we can't fight each other or other players is at the end of the section, and it isn't bold or otherwise called out. Notice the "each other" part. That means Guides can't attack Guides. But yet the Guides on Lanys are all PvP flagged, and there is a PvP area in cshome, and the Guides very often swing at each other in a playful manner. In other words, one part of the sentence is not enforced, but instead encouraged, while the next part of the sentence gets you banned instantly with no chance to explain yourself, and insulted at the same time. <P>After being informed how bad of people we were, we were stripped of our Guide status, disconnected, and our entire account suspended. I haven't been able to log in since then, and worse yet can't order RoK because you have to log in to do that. But the story gets worse. <P>Granted I'm a bit biased. Call me crazy but I still enjoy playing the game. I was upset about being treated the way I was, but I have a guild to run with my primary character, and I was looking forward to RoK just as much as anyone. So I sent an email to the Head GM, as I was told to do, and as is normal in a situation like this. But remember this is the the GM that kicked us out in the first place. Her name is Cailleach in game, I won't give her real name or email address. Here's what I sent: <P>--------------- <P><I>Even though I have many thoughts and comments about your decision and their effect on me, I'll keep them to myself. Please remove the banning from my account so I can continue playing my characters on my home servers. <P>username: ******* <P>Also please inform me whether I should purchase the RoK online. I don't want to waste money if I already have a copy on the way due to my former guide status, however slim the chance. <P>Also let me know if there are any further actions I must take in order to continue playing my normal characters back on my normal server, with people that I respect. <P>Lastly, I urge you to revisit your training procedures and the PnP, so that other potential guides are better informed and won't have to go through the same bullshit ordeal I did because of your lousy documentation. Do you honestly think that five different people would all take part in an activity they knew was illegal, and not even mention that fact? And do you feel that a guide of less than 24 hours would know every detail, and question an order or suggestion by his superior? If my actions were a disgrace to Guiding, then your actions are a disgrace to Verant and GM's. And that is not an insult, merely an observation. <P><P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:32 2000] Cailleach says, 'You are a disgrace.' <P><P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:05 2000] Cailleach says, 'That is not an insult, merely an observation.' <P>Jer ******, a.k.a. Desmo the Murdered, former guide of Lanys, RIP <P>--------------- <P>And here is what I got in return: <P><b>Your whole attitude about this justifies my decision to refuse to allow you to return, if you ask me. Your account was not banned. It was suspended. I have no idea if Kunark has been sent to you or not, but I'm not going to be concerned about it if it was. <P>Thanks, <P>-- <P>************ <br>Head Game Master <br>Verant Interactive <br>**********@verant.com </b><br></i>-------------- <P>And that's where it is at now. I've honestly pretty much forgotten about it. Hopefully my account will be back up and running tomorrow. Overall, I agree I screwed up by breaking a rule. But I believe the punishment should suit the crime. I would expect to be reprimanded a little, perhaps a message put up on the Guide forums reminding people of the policy, and finally me being watched a little closer to make sure I wasn't a "bad apple." But what did happen was totally uncalled for. I didn't know I would get to play for free when I signed up to be a guide, I didn't know that we would get RoK for free, and I sure as hell didn't know I would be treated like complete dog crap by Verant. I applied to be a Guide because I enjoy helping others. I volunteered more than the required 10 hours per week because I was having fun doing it. <P>To the other Guides on Lanys, I wish you the best. You were all very friendly people, and helpful to a new guide like myself. To Jhek, Lead GM of Lanys, even though you work for Verant, I know you went to bat for me and did what you could. I think you are the best GM I've ever dealt with, and others share my opinion. To any of the other Guides that were banned with me and feel somewhat guilty, don't sweat it. I have no hard feelings towards you at all. To all the rest of Verant that agrees what happened to me was justified, I return to you my Sword of Guidance. <P>Former Guide Desmo, currently just another player like the rest of you. <P>Log of the Event:</b><P>----------- <P>[Thu Apr 06 21:52:57 2000] You have been summoned by the gods!<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:52:57 2000] LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:53:14 2000] You have entered Sunset Home.<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:53:21 2000] You say, 'Hail'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:53:22 2000] Axgoreth says, 'Have a seat Desmo'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:53:25 2000] Calais says, 'what section of the Pnp please?'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:53:41 2000] Cailleach says, 'You are not to be engaging in combat with players or one another while in your guide character.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:53:48 2000] Cailleach says, 'Are you unaware of that?'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:53:52 2000] Ozzadyen says, 'Then why are we all PVP/'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:53:59 2000] Tanden tells the guild, 'Guys if they kick Ozza, who's for camping right then and letting them run this server until they get him back? :)'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:54:09 2000] Aidan tells you, 'whats up man you guys didnt get in too much trouble i hope......'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:54:11 2000] Cailleach says, 'There is really no point discussing this.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:54:18 2000] Calais says, 'what section please?'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:54:21 2000] You say, 'I was unaware, yes. I knew teh Apps couldn't, didn't read it for Guides though'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:54:27 2000] Tanden tells the guild, 'This is bullshit, NOWHERE in this P&P does it state we may not participate in player quests/events'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:54:33 2000] Cailleach says, 'No one can. And it will never happen again.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:54:36 2000] Ozzadyen says, 'of course I know there is no Point I am wrong you are right. Was a pleasure serving the last year.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:55:17 2000] Cailleach says, 'I'm sorry, but you are not going to delay this asking for the section numbers. '<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:55:25 2000] Cailleach says, 'All full guides get this in their initial training.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:55:26 2000] Calais says, 'ok'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:55:31 2000] Cailleach says, 'Before they become apprentices.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:55:35 2000] It begins to rain.<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:55:40 2000] Cailleach says, 'Or they do not become apprentices.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:55:46 2000] Cailleach says, 'It is as simple as that.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:56:03 2000] Ozzadyen tells the guild, 'Guys everyone I am sorry looks like we will all be released for this :('<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:56:16 2000] Tanden tells the guild, 'Not if I have anything to do with it'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:56:17 2000] Athelan says, 'PnP Section 5.4.7'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:56:47 2000] Calais GMSAYS, 'well... hmm there goes the fun...'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:56:59 2000] Tanden GMSAYS, 'Axe, where in the P&P does it state that guides may not participate in player run events?'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:03 2000] Cailleach says, 'I will stand by any guide when they do their job. However. When this kind of thing happens, I can't support you.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:21 2000] Axgoreth GMSAYS, 'Athelan just answered that question.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:23 2000] You say, 'Yep, it does say it there. I'm sorry I missed it the first time I read it thru'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:32 2000] Cailleach says, 'You are a disgrace.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:39 2000] Lyzza has defeated Debranis in a duel to the death!<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:42 2000] Cailleach frowns.<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:49 2000] Ozzadyen tells the guild, 'hahaha I am a disgrace wonderful'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:53 2000] Calais says, 'do not insult us.. we messed up and that is fine but do not insult us'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:57:56 2000] Tanden GMSAYS, 'No he didn't'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:05 2000] Cailleach says, 'That is not an insult, merely an observation.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:06 2000] Tanden GMSAYS, 'I never saw it'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:08 2000] Tanden GMSAYS, 'Please say it in /pr'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:08 2000] Valdul GMSAYS, 'section 5.4.7'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:11 2000] Calais says, 'i have a few my self then'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:19 2000] Cailleach says, 'Feel free to email me.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:20 2000] Athelan says, 'Quote "Guides do not fight each other or players, no matter the circumstances, outside of scripted quests, only ath the direction of the Quest Elder, and NEVER with their guide character."'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:31 2000] You say to your guild, 'woah there Cal, let them talk first'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:35 2000] Calais says, 'oh i will and evryone edsle int he bbok'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:37 2000] Cailleach says, 'You will be removed.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:41 2000] Athelan says, 'That is from the PnP.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:42 2000] Cailleach says, 'Immediately.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:48 2000] Cailleach says, 'That is the bottom line.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:58:58 2000] Tanden tells the guild, 'damn'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:59:06 2000] Tygira nods in understanding.<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:59:11 2000] Tygira says, 'I'm sorry.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:59:17 2000] Calais says, 'as am i....'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:59:30 2000] Cailleach says, 'If so, why were you arguing the way you were? I cannot understand that.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:59:39 2000] Cailleach says, 'We don't make arbitrary decisions. '<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:59:44 2000] Calais says, 'i never argued just didnt want to be insulted'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:59:55 2000] Calais says, 'i messed up but dont like being called names'<P>[Thu Apr 06 21:59:59 2000] Cailleach says, 'We follow the guidelines that were set up with the approval of the guide program.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:00:15 2000] Cailleach says, 'You did, Calais. You were the one who challenged us to prove it was wrong by giving you chapter and verse of the P&P'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:00:27 2000] Calais says, 'just so i could reasdd it'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:00:28 2000] Cailleach says, 'Do you feel you are a good exqample?'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:00:30 2000] Calais says, 'i could find it'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:00:33 2000] Cailleach says, 'I certainly don't.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:00:36 2000] Tygira says, 'I have no arguement. I did wrong and will accept any consequenses for it. I admit, I do not want to be removed, but I will respect your decision as to mypunishment.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:00:49 2000] Cailleach says, 'I spent a lot of time in the guide program, and I knew it was wrong. Did you not care enough to learn it?'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:00:53 2000] Calais says, 'not to argue just to read it because i couldnt find it'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:01:23 2000] You say, 'I have been a full Guide for one day, I was still learning, as I thought we all were'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:01:23 2000] Cailleach says, 'Say goodbye to CS Home. If you wish to protest your removals, feel free, but I'm afraid it won't do much good with this much blatant violation.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:01:49 2000] Tygira cries.<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:01:50 2000] Calais says, 'are we all being rmeoved or just me?'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:01:56 2000] Cailleach says, 'All of you who were involved.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:02:02 2000] Calais says, 'ahh..'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:02:32 2000] Calais GMSAYS, 'well see ya guys..... nice to know ya'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:02:37 2000] Cailleach says, 'Your guide chars will be removed.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:02:38 2000] Desmo picked a bad night to volunteer his services for the good of EQ.<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:03:09 2000] You GMSAY, 'Aye, was a pleasure.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:03:16 2000] Valdul GMSAYS, 'It sure was.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:03:20 2000] Cailleach says, 'I wish to hear no more from you at this time. If you have anything further to say, please email me. You can do so at ********@verant.com'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:03:21 2000] Athelan says, 'You made a bad choice and broke the policies which you are supposed to abide by'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:03:34 2000] Axgoreth sighs, clearly disappointed.<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:04:41 2000] Tygira cries.<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:04:55 2000] Tygira says, 'Goodbye everyone. I'm sorry. I failed you as your trainer.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:05:03 2000] Valdul says, 'You failed nothing.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:05:10 2000] Calais says, 'you didnt.... no biggie'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:05:21 2000] You say, 'I have no hard feeling towards you Tyg'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:06:14 2000] You say to your guild, 'no more free Kunark I bet....'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:06:24 2000] Calais says, 'hhehe nope'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:06:41 2000] You told ********, 'you there?'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:06:56 2000] Valdul tells the guild, 'Well i guess since we are not head honchos ina big company Verant cares nothing for their customers feelings.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:07:52 2000] You told ********, 'please respond'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:07:59 2000] Calais says, 'i ahve all your emails ill keep in touch'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:08:01 2000] ******** tells you, 'sorry was fighting yes im here'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:08:07 2000] Valdul tells the guild, 'Same Calais.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:08:07 2000] Calais says, 'see ya tygira'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:08:20 2000] Tygira says, 'Goodbye Calais. I'm sorry.'<P>[Thu Apr 06 22:08:34 2000] You told *******, 'Please tell your guild that all the Guides in the Arena have been banned. We aren't too happy.'<P>YOU HAVE BEEN DISCONNECTED</UL><P>To voice your opinion of this issue please leave a news comment or visit the new <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?mes=5435001&replies=0">special board thread</a> I have created on the Player Views Board. 

